 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Server Platform Application Engineer Intel 5,431 reviews Hillsboro, OR 97124 Intel 5,431 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Job Description 
Come join the Platform Application Engineering team in Intel's Server division. You will be conducting multidisciplinary work in the customer enabling team to grow your skillset in server manageability firmware enabling and debug. 
Your specific role will have opportunity to but not limited to the following: 
Influence new product definitions, assist customer in building Xeon based servers by delivering design specs, technical training. 
Debugging and resolving firmware issues and working closely with customers in resolving their issues. 
Initiate and contribute to overall design and development of new ideas and products and impact company's revenue by helping customers launch their products on time. 
Work closely with different teams within Intel to create documentation and collateral for customer enabling as well as work with teams across multiple geos in defining the customer enabling process. 
The ideal candidate will be: 
Highly motivated self-starter 
Collaborative team player with strong interpersonal skills. 
Excellent communicator 
Comfortable working in a fast-paced environment 
Qualifications 
Minimum Qualifications 
Bachelor's degree or higher in Electrical Engineering or Computer Science or related 
6+ months experience through internships or course work in Computer Architecture and Operating Systems. 
6+ months experience of either Python/C/C++ programming. 
Inside this Business Group 
The Data Platforms Engineering and Architecture (DPEA) Group invents, designs & builds the world's most critical computing platforms which fuel Intel's most important business and solve the world's most fundamental problems. DPEA enables that data center which is the underpinning for every data-driven service, from artificial intelligence to 5G to high-performance computing, and DCG delivers the products and technologiesâ€”spanning software, processors, storage, I/O, and networking solutionsâ€”that fuel cloud, communications, enterprise, and government data centers around the world. 
